document.title: Ohio's Early Learning and Development Standards

32F48752A79940BFA81F2B212AD0A25B.description:
Show ability to transfer
and manipulate an object
with hands

65C30D3A572C4DB9BEDF59876F0C6D32.description:
Attend and respond when
familiar books are read aloud.

5A63D64DB57A45C58B7D6DDB5A24F064.description:
Show interest in books, pictures,
songs and rhymes.

8F376ADC29684975A6A828C776536760.description:
Attempt to respond to basic forms
of social communication with
the appropriate facial expression,
vocalization and/or gesture.

927EE0DA13E542998A9CE1EE4AEDC28A.description:
Experiment intentionally with
sound inflection and gestures in
different ways to express wants,
needs or feelings.

506353F0E5A6464089AE40BB792AF685.description:
Attend and respond to language
and sounds.

76648F948911450284B16C364E79CCC9.description:
Use simple actions to make
things happen.

9DD4C8FA059E410C8330CBB430DE942D.description:
Observe, hold, touch and
manipulate objects.

D6379EAC0C0841F198A79991CB60F5DF.description:
Examine objects with lips
and tongue.

22C7CE22BDED4FAB84F9D188D9EDD927.description:
Show awareness of self and
awareness of other people.

AA55E8E1D52C47F8858FB35140208BEC.description: Cognition and General Knowledge: Social Studies

2CF62A7C1BFE46C7A71FCC3D57DA9AC2.description:
Notice differences between
familiar and unfamiliar people,
objects and places.

BE94EEC730A24B51916612FD5C1366A7.description:
Explore objects and attend to
events in the environment.

30672255068845369C588FC0A20ED07D.description:
Explore objects and attend to
events in the environment.

0AB2C4AD1BCA401CB0E6A8AA82D8D33D.description:
Actively use the body to find out
about the world.

334679E8AAF741DAA2D062B686A31151.description:
Explore real objects, people
and actions.

3EC53F7034FF4E638F8F9A55B2BEACDD.description:
Anticipate next steps in simple
familiar routines and games.

97D0C209E72E480BB63EA9C47C993016.description:
Mirror simple actions and facial
expressions of others previously
experienced.

6C83CEA52C174DFA971C1368BBECDE9C.description:
Exhibit differentiated responses
to familiar and unfamiliar people,
events, objects and their features.

9C83F29DEBC54AF38EF7610504998D5C.description:
Interact with adults in physical
activities.

8F85B84DCDE24275AF016355D8D695C0.description:
Use senses and movement to
explore immediate surroundings.

7CB8EE0C471B42C5A00DCD72FD90FEE0.description:
Open mouth to wait for food
to enter and use upper lip to
clean food off spoon during
spoon feeding.

2172815E35154BB78825660783F174E8.description:
Use mouth and tongue to
explore objects.

7D4CB6A35C694F6A922E16306F213AA7.description:
Transfer a toy from one hand to
another by reaching, grasping
and releasing.

93ABF97D44E84E969510DE5ECFE22EA6.description: Small Muscle: Touch, Grasp, Reach, Manipulate

0F7C3609B7F84CCA8CA3AA52DD3448D1.description:
Demonstrate strength and control
of head, arms, legs and trunk
using purposeful movements.

C59E873FE0E040B0AB49A868F3920C08.description:
Demonstrate preferences,
pleasure or displeasure when
interacting with various media.

5235CDBBEA1645808688E3FBDF098EA5.description: Expression of Ideas and Feelings Through the Arts

C31E056284DF45C2B18C635F7F0C386F.description:
Make discoveries about self,
others, and the environment.

5C69E9F9F8FF47A4BAC1251768D5E728.description:
Attempt to reproduce
interesting and pleasurable
effects and events.

60584B9CE3BE48D6A35D2BF41D79CA25.description:
Demonstrate awareness of
happenings in surroundings.

C928E15BF26143E49C6E3C53269B9407.description:
Respond to people and objects
in their immediate environment
based on past experience.

2C57468493DF425F81ACE830CD9C14BB.description:
Act on the environment to meet
needs or interests.

2049D7D5DCD7455093A1E730DF0F7E40.description:
Show interest in people and
objects.

D808AC156D4E46F69448D55D9CE9A357.description:
React to emotional expressions
of others

8C9D7C08268241DA8FACE23F827A9455.description:
Repeat actions that elicit social
responses from others.

E1A20FA26EA74CC5A145E1F00E3AA146.description:
Initiate and engage in reciprocal
(mutual give and take) interactions
with familiar adults.

E35E910D603444ED82BEC1CF9B89EDFB.description:
Initiate interactions and seek close
proximity to familiar adults who
provide consistent nurturing.

4AC280B5A2D9424C97B0C99B8EF950A4.description: Act in ways to make things happen.

BBD8E7CD7A384E4DBBC7EAB9537B1035.description:
Comfort self in simple ways and
communicate needs for help
through vocalizations
and gestures.

09197C9FBA9243C9BD60CA19CC7D3BF1.description:
Begin to understand self as a
separate person from others.

78B3CB325B0E4916A51416105FE644FD.description:
Express a variety of emotions
(contentment, distress, happiness,
sadness, surprise, dislike,
anger and fear) through facial
expressions, gestures, movement
and sounds.
